I liked both Shout! and Barney Miller.
However, these discs have difficulty being read at all, with me needing to open and restart the DVD player or computer multiple times before the discs will play.
And telling my DVD player to [ALL REPEAT] plays the same [CHAPTER/Episode] over and over again.
I am guessing this is some bizarre form of copy protection, but it makes these discs less than ideal for watching.
i will have to rethink buying any more Shout! products.

Although Barney Miller accurately captures the 70s in New York, at least as I remember that era, the show also addresses issues that were far ahead of its times.  Yet, it still remained funny while dealing with serious themes.  Recommended.

I found out after Season 3 ..the show was a Liberal agenda and not an enjoyable comedy TV show ..you could relax and just enjoy ..I do not care how your political views are ..I feel it should be like All in the Family ..both sides of politics made you laugh ..Not so in Barney Miller 4th Season or the 5 th ..I could not believe it ..it was not funny anymore ..sorry I got Season 4 & 5 should have stopped at the 3rd year ...this is just my 2 cents worth ..you might like it ..I am just expressing my view.
